{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
The '''golden triangle''' is an informal [[Finnish language|Finnish]]-[[English language|English]] term for the area of southwestern [[Finland]] between the cities of [[Helsinki]], [[Turku]], and [[Tampere]] where most of the country's population, arable land, and GDP is done.

