{{Expand Spanish|Reserva Botánica Regional Huckleberry|topic=geo|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox park | name = Huckleberry Botanic Regional Preserve | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | map = <!-- or | map_image = --> | map_width = | type = Botanical preserve | location = San Francisco Bay Area, California | nearest_city = Oakland, California | coordinates = | area = {{convert|241|acre|km2}} | created = | operator = East Bay Regional Park District | visitation_num = | status = | designation = | open = }} [[File:Chrysolepis chrysophylla Huckleberry BRP 1.jpg|thumb|225px|[[Chrysolepis#Species|Golden chinquapin]] (''Chrysolepis chrysophylla''), at the Preserve in the [[Berkeley Hills]].]] [[File:Papilio eurymedon 000.jpg|thumb|225px|[[Papilio eurymedon|Pale Swallowtail]] butterfly (''Papilio eurymedon'') at the Huckleberry Botanic Preserve]] '''Huckleberry Botanic Regional Preserve''' is a {{convert|241|acre|km2}} [[regional park]] and [[nature reserve]] in the [[Berkeley Hills]], in the eastern [[East Bay (San Francisco Bay Area)]] region of the [[San Francisco Bay Area]] of [[California]]. It is within [[Alameda County, California|Alameda]] and [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa Counties]].<ref name="ebrpd">[http://www.ebparks.org/parks/huckleberry EBRPD-huckleberry "Huckleberry Botanic Regional Preserve." East Bay Regional Parks District] Accessed November 1, 2011</ref> It is a park within the [[East Bay Regional Parks District]] system.<ref name="ebrpd"/> The Preserve is named after the [[Vaccinium ovatum|California Huckleberry]] (''Vaccinium ovatum'') which grows abundantly within its [[habitat]].<ref name="ebrpd"/>
==Geography== The Huckleberry Botanic Regional Preserve is on the crest of the [[Oakland Hills]], located above [[Oakland, California|Oakland]] and [[Orinda, California|Orinda]]. It represents a relic plant association found only in certain areas along the coastal climate region of California, where specific soil and climatic conditions still exist.<ref name="ebrpd"/> It is a very diverse botanical area for [[native plant]]s of the [[California mixed evergreen forest|mixed evergreen forest]] and [[California montane chaparral and woodlands|montane chaparral and woodlands]] [[ecoregion]]s and [[plant community|plant communities]]. Trails connect the preserve with [[Robert Sibley Volcanic Preserve]] on the north, and Redwood Regional Park on the south.<ref name="OWiki">[https://oaklandwiki.org/Huckleberry_Botanic_Regional_Preserve "Huckleberry Botanic Regional Preserve." Oakland Wiki.] Accessed September 1, 2017.</ref>
The Huckleberry Trail is a {{convert|1.7|mile|km}} self-guided nature path that loops through the Preserve.<ref name="ebrpd"/> Besides the California Huckleberry, other plants include the [[Chrysolepis#Species|Golden chinquapin]] (''Chrysolepis chrysophylla''), and [[Umbellularia|California Bay]] (''Umbellularia californica'') and [[Coast live oak]] (''Quercus agrifolia'') woodlands.<ref name="ebrpd"/>
==Visitation== The park is open year-round, between 5:00 AM and 10:00 PM daily, unless otherwise posted. No dogs are permitted in the park because of the sensitive plant habitat. There are no reservable campgrounds or picnic sites. Parking is free.<ref name="ebrpd"/>
==See also== *[[California mixed evergreen forest]] *[[List of California native plants]] *[[Vaccinium ovatum]]
